title: Hearty Cioppino
summary: Hearty Cioppino might be just the main course you are searching for. This recipe makes 6 servings with 277 calories, 24g of protein, and 9g of fat each. For $3.15 per serving, this recipe covers 28% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. Only a few people made this recipe, and 1 would say it hit the spot. instructions: Cook onion, fennel, and chiles in oil over medium heat in a Dutch oven until onion is tender. Add bell pepper and garlic; cook, stirring constantly, 3 minutes. Stir in tomatoes and next 5 ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat, and simmer 45 minutes.                                                                                                Stir in zucchini and rosemary; bring to a simmer, and simmer 10 minutes. Remove and discard bay leaf. Stir in salt and pepper.                                                                                                Add scallops and shrimp, and cook 3 minutes. Add mussels and fish; cook 4 more minutes or until mussels open and fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

steps.step: Cook onion, fennel, and chiles in oil over medium heat in a Dutch oven until onion is tender.
Add bell pepper and garlic; cook, stirring constantly, 3 minutes. Stir in tomatoes and next 5 ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat, and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in zucchini and rosemary; bring to a simmer, and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaf. Stir in salt and pepper.
Add scallops and shrimp, and cook 3 minutes.
Add mussels and fish; cook 4 more minutes or until mussels open and fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
